spx.packets

Interface Type


  • public interface Type
    Define the packetType values for SPxPacketHeaderB headers.

    These can be in the range 0 to 65535, but to keep them unique with the type A headers we don't use the 0 to 255 range.

    Future possibilities are endless but include index/table-of-contents etc.

    These constants are kept in sync with the SPX_PACKET_TYPEB_... constants in "SPxPackets.h".
